# Config Style

- Use `@Configuration` classes for bean wiring and cross-cutting setup.
- Keep bean methods explicit and focused (`ModelMapper`, auth manager, password encoder, filters).
- Prefer straightforward fluent Spring config over custom abstraction layers.
- Keep startup data bootstrapping in dedicated components (`CommandLineRunner`) with idempotent checks.
- Treat environment-driven behavior via `@Value` flags and branch clearly by environment intent.
